Wang Yuxiang runs a travel agency in Hungary. He lost his parents long ago, but now has a Hungarian mother who has given him a feeling of family. Dr. Chen Xinhua runs a hospital in Phnom Penh, Cambodia, but has achieved success in much more than just business, forging a connection with the life and people there. The Belt and Road Initiative has given millions of Chinese people like them new lives across the globe, and an ever closer connection to their second homes.